3.how is playwright different from selenium or cypress?
Selenium is a traditional tool that uses WebDriver and needs more manual waits, Cypress is fast and easy
to set up but has limitations like no Safari support and limited handling of multiple tabs. whereas Playwright is more modern, it has auto-waiting 
by default, supports Chromium, Firefox, and WebKit for Safari testing, and handles real-world scenarios like iframes and multiple tabs easily. 

Flaky Tests:
Flaky tests are automated tests that sometimes pass and sometimes fail without any change in the application code.
Reason:
Timing issues – element not loaded yet, animations, slow API response
Missing or incorrect waits
Network or environment instability
Dynamic elements (changing IDs, text, or data)
Test dependency – one test depends on another

